  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with axillary osmidrosis are treated with minimally invasive procedure combined
      tumescent liposuction with Subcutaneous Pruning. Effectiveness of this modified method in
      reducing odor is to be determined.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with excessive malodor are recruited. They are surgically treated with minimally
      invasive procedure combined tumescent liposuction with Subcutaneous Pruning and followed up
      for 6-24 months to evaluate effectiveness sand side effect.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
